               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t16890516-33-defend160" type="defendantName">
                  Martin 
                  Powel
               <interp inst="t16890516-33-defend160" type="surname" value="Powel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16890516-33-defend160" type="given" value="Martin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16890516-33-defend160" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             
                  <rs id="t16890516-33-deflabel150" type="occupation">Gent.</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t16890516-33-defend160 t16890516-33-deflabel150"></join> of <placeName id="t16890516-33-defloc151">St. Andrews Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t16890516-33-defloc151" type="placeName" value="St. Andrews Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t16890516-33-defloc151" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16890516-33-defend160 t16890516-33-defloc151"></join>, was Tryed for <rs id="t16890516-33-off152" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16890516-33-off152" type="offenceCategory" value="kill"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16890516-33-off152" type="offenceSubcategory" value="murder"></interp>
               Feloniously and Wilfully Murthering (with a Rapier value 5 s.) 
                     
                        <persName id="t16890516-33-victim162" type="victimName">
                           Thomas 
                           Ward
                        <interp inst="t16890516-33-victim162" type="surname" value="Ward"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16890516-33-victim162" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16890516-33-victim162" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16890516-33-off152 t16890516-33-victim162"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , giving him one Morral Wound near his left Pap. of the depth of 4 Inches, of which he died on the 6th instant
            </rs>. Upon the Evidence it was declared, That the Prisoner met with the deceased in the Night time amongst others, where was a Quarrel about some Women, and in the midst of it Ward lost his Life the Prisoner's Sword was Bloody, which was produced in Court, but it was alledged that the deceased was Wounded before Powel was ingaged in the Quarrel, and that he was abused and urged draw his Sword, which was Witnessed by some whom the Pris called: But Powel's Sword, as before was found bloody in hand, and that Ward did say before his Death, That Powel give him the Wound. Yet the Evidence against him was strenuous enough to fix it upon him: So was found <rs id="t16890516-33-verdict153" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16890516-33-verdict153" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16890516-33-verdict153" type="verdictSubcategory" value="manslaughter"></interp>
               Guilty of M slaughter only
            </rs>.</p>
